Privacy Policy for SSHMatrix

Last Updated: February 24, 2026

Thank you for using SSHMatrix. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how SSHMatrix (“we”, “our”, or “us”) handles information when you use our Android live wallpaper application.

1. Overview

SSHMatrix is a live wallpaper application for Android devices. We are committed to collecting as little data as possible. The app does not collect personal information, does not require user registration, and does not store personal data.

The only data collected relates to app stability and in-app purchases, as described below.

2. Information We Collect
A. Crash and Performance Data

SSHMatrix collects limited, non-personal information related to app crashes and performance issues.

This may include:

Device model

Android OS version

App version

Crash logs

General diagnostic information

This information:

Is used solely to improve app stability and performance

Does not personally identify you

Is typically collected through Google Play’s crash reporting tools or similar Android system services

We do not link crash data to individual users.

B. In-App Purchases

SSHMatrix offers optional locked content that can be unlocked via in-app purchases using the Google Play In-App Billing API.

When you make a purchase:

Payment processing is handled entirely by Google

We do not receive or store your payment information (such as credit card details)

We only receive confirmation that a purchase was successfully completed

For more information on how Google handles payment data, please refer to Google’s Privacy Policy.

3. Data Sharing

We do not:

Sell user data

Share personal data with third parties

Use personal data for advertising

Crash data may be processed by Google Play services solely for analytics and stability purposes.

4. Data Retention

Crash and diagnostic information is retained only as long as necessary to:

Identify issues

Improve performance

Maintain app stability

We do not maintain personal user profiles or databases.

5. Children’s Privacy

SSHMatrix does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. Since we do not collect personal data, the app is considered low risk in terms of privacy exposure.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us and we will address the issue promptly.

6. Security

We rely on:

Android system security

Google Play services

Secure Google billing infrastructure

We do not store sensitive personal data on our servers.

7. Your Rights

Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights regarding your data. However, since we do not collect personally identifiable information, there is generally no personal data for us to access, modify, or delete.

For purchase-related data, please refer to your Google Play account settings.

8. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected with a new “Last Updated” date. Continued use of SSHMatrix after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
